All Norwegian jäger rifles in fairly good condition were converted to percussion in 1841 and in 1851 they were converted to pillar breech rifles in order to enable faster loading and use of pointed bullets. They were also fitted with a new rear sight, a new bayonet and a new ramrod.

title: For Sale/Trade:  (UPDATED) WWII Kukri Bring Back
location: Elk River, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent: Up For Sale or Trade is a WWII Kukri Bring Back, it was my Grandfathers, who passed it down to me, the Blade is exactly 12.5 inches long, the hilt is made of Buffalo Horn and Ivory, it comes with the original sheath and Sharpeners which is in decent shape for its age. I have had a request for Authentication Paperwork, and after speaking with a Couple of Gentlemen that specialize in items like these, they both went on to tell me to find the original history and the exact date it was created would be virtually impossible without Provenance, or the location it was actually created, or a name of who made it.  They both went on to ask me why I would need an authentication, and I said for possible sale or trade, and this is what they told me-  It is in fact authentic and would date it around WWII or a little earlier, based on the width of the Sheath and its Thickness, probably around the late thirties, earlier sheaths are much slimmer in thickness and if fact much wider. The Next Indication of the time period are the carrying Lugs (or The loops that hook to your belt) are made in the "V" design which is also typical or the WWII Era designs. The later designed Carrying Lugs are Vertical Double Loops, or a single wide Loop, and according to the Blade width it is typical of a Government Issue Blade. The blade is Wicked sharp and according to my Grandfather as long as hes had it has never been sharpend. They Also said it is more than likely a Kothimora White, which was typical for Officers to carry. I have researched their assessment to find it 100% accurate, feel free to research it yourself. If you need more proof than these facts about what time frame it’s from, I don't know what to tell you.Shoot me some offers, lets make a deal.
